WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.000
This is a synthetic pre-flight QA demo for a Shopify brand.

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:09.000
It is not connected to a client Gorgias account, and it is not a client case study.

00:00:09.000 --> 00:00:12.000
The commercial scope is deliberately narrow.

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:17.000
One Shopify store, one Gorgias inbox, and two high-volume skills.

00:00:17.000 --> 00:00:19.000
Where is my order and return requests?

00:00:19.000 --> 00:00:23.000
These 15 synthetic tickets show the evaluation structure.

00:00:23.000 --> 00:00:31.000
This order status case uses order context and approved policy sources to produce a test-only draft.

00:00:31.000 --> 00:00:33.000
No shopper message is sent.

00:00:33.000 --> 00:00:35.000
Returns are not all the same.

00:00:35.000 --> 00:00:37.000
A policy question may produce a draft.

00:00:37.000 --> 00:00:43.000
An eligible return that needs a label stays with the person because an admin action is required.

00:00:43.000 --> 00:00:48.000
An out-of-window refund request is escalated because goodwill is a business decision.

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:59.000
The same handover rule applies to lost packages, damaged items, chargeback threats, missing data, or any answer that cannot be grounded in approved sources.

00:00:59.000 --> 00:01:05.000
A paid sprint does not treat synthetic counts as performance. In seven days, I use 50 to 100 anonymized historical tickets to build the test matrix.

00:01:05.000 --> 00:01:18.000
I audit Gorgias Knowledge, Guidance, Skills, tone, and handover rules, then run representative cases in Gorgias Test mode.

00:01:18.000 --> 00:01:29.000
Your reviewer scores draft acceptance, major edits, routing agreement, unsafe false negatives, median review time, and unhandled cases.

00:01:29.000 --> 00:01:32.000
Any unsafe false negative blocks go-live.

00:01:32.000 --> 00:01:36.000
The fixed design-partner sprint is $750.

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:42.000
It ends with the scorecard, failure log, change log, SOP, and a go or no-go decision.

00:01:42.000 --> 00:01:54.266
If Gorgias setup quality or launch risk is the blocker, let’s take 15 minutes to see whether this scope fits.
